            <fr:title text="The category of thinnings">The category of thinnings</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A <html:em>scope</html:em> is a list of variable names, and a <html:em>thinning</html:em> is an
order-preserving embedding of one scope into another, as in McBride's
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/mcbrideEverybodysGotToBeSomewhere2018/" title="Everybody's Got To Be Somewhere" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/mcbrideEverybodysGotToBeSomewhere2018/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/mcbrideEverybodysGotToBeSomewhere2018/" type="local">Everybody's Got To Be Somewhere</fr:link>.</html:p>
            <html:p>Scopes exist to scope <html:em>terms</html:em>: over a scope <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathit {xs}]]></fr:tex>, one
may define terms for describing a
<fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G9/" title="Unification by Löb induction over thinnings" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G9/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00G9/" type="local">first-order unification algorithm</fr:link>
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[t \;::=\; \mathsf {var}\ x
   \;\mid \; \mathsf {leaf}
   \;\mid \; \mathsf {fork}\ t\ t,]]></fr:tex>
with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> a variable of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathit {xs}]]></fr:tex>, and a thinning embedding the
terms over its source into the terms over its target.
</html:p>
            <html:p>The category is <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FG/" title="Direct categories" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FG/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FG/" type="local">direct</fr:link> with degree given by the length of the
scope. It is <html:em>not</html:em> <fr:link href="/foreign/stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FH/" title="Well-founded posets are thin direct categories" uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FH/" display-uri="https://stevenschaefer.net/sss-00FH/" type="local">thin</fr:link>, as there are two thinnings
from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [A\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [A , A\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
